Kriel in Mpumalanga is now the world’s second biggest hotspot of sulphur dioxide emissions. That’s according to new data released on Monday. Courtesy #DStv403 KRIEL - Kriel in Mpumalanga has been named the world's second biggest sulphur dioxide emissions hotspot. READ: Mpumalanga identified as world's biggest air pollution hotspot The new data comes from NASA satellites, released on Monday morning. Greenpeace India commissioned the study to track SO2 hotspots around the globe. Mpumalanga is home to 12 coal-fired power plants. The satellite data also shows that Johannesburg and Pretoria are affected by the pollution, which blows across from Mpumalanga.